WEBVTT

00:02.360 --> 00:04.860
How many times have I told you,
your store is growing too quickly.

00:04.939 --> 00:05.700
You've never told me that.

00:05.810 --> 00:06.670
Your books are a mess.

00:06.780 --> 00:07.950
When have you ever seen my books?

00:08.100 --> 00:09.210
I haven't seen your books,but I know you.

00:09.320 --> 00:10.040
Let's focus,please.

00:10.130 --> 00:12.080
Look,my friend kylie's a financial whiz.

00:12.240 --> 00:13.430
She could really help you.

00:13.500 --> 00:16.740
Her father was the dean of the
business school here before he died.

00:16.830 --> 00:19.410
Before that,he was my economics department advisor.

00:19.590 --> 00:22.460
- You were an economics major?
- Yes,I was an economics major.

00:22.580 --> 00:24.470
I was this close to getting my undergrad,ok?

00:24.650 --> 00:25.480
In economics?

00:25.600 --> 00:28.500
Yes,I can add,melinda.I'm a big boy,ok?

00:28.580 --> 00:31.000
Look,kylie lost her merit scholarship.

00:31.110 --> 00:32.509
That's her loss,but it's your gain.

00:32.600 --> 00:33.690
Does she have the job or not?

00:33.790 --> 00:35.590
Well,she might have,but she's a half an hour late,

00:35.670 --> 00:36.780
and it's my night to cook.

00:36.900 --> 00:38.950
Well,I think I told her 7:30.

00:38.960 --> 00:39.880
You cook?What do you cook?

00:39.970 --> 00:40.480
Tell me about it.

00:40.610 --> 00:43.100
Well,I make a great lasagna,you told her 7:00,

00:43.180 --> 00:44.840
and I can't hire someone who's flaky.

00:45.190 --> 00:46.080
She's not flaky.

00:46.220 --> 00:48.490
She's not.She's just.

00:48.650 --> 00:49.570
she's troubled.

