04:02.140 --> 04:05.170
Hey,this student that you hired,what's her deal?

04:05.590 --> 04:08.270
Uh,her name's kylie,her grades slipped,

04:08.400 --> 04:10.820
and she's trying to get her scholarship reinstated.

04:11.040 --> 04:12.760
I'm talking about her other deal.

04:13.150 --> 04:14.520
What's the reason we hired her?

04:14.860 --> 04:16.459
Well,I thought we weren't gonna talk about it.

04:16.579 --> 04:18.890
You were just gonna do your thing,
I was gonna do my thing,yada yada.

04:19.040 --> 04:21.620
Yeah,except your thing kinda becomes my thing

04:21.740 --> 04:23.030
when you bring it into the store.

04:23.120 --> 04:25.800
Well,is it really going to bother you that much
even if you don't believe it's real?

04:25.920 --> 04:29.450
No,I was just,you know,trying to know
how I should act around her.

04:29.590 --> 04:32.220
I don't want to step on any ghost toes.

04:32.580 --> 04:33.640
Well,I really appreciate that.

04:33.760 --> 04:35.950
Um,she has a ghost.

04:36.170 --> 04:38.040
That's pretty much all I know so far.

04:38.170 --> 04:41.400
Ok.Hey,I just want to remind you
that I've got that appointment

04:41.530 --> 04:44.100
with ned on thursday,so I won't be here all day.

04:44.210 --> 04:44.690
I've got it.

04:44.860 --> 04:45.910
It's on the calendar.

04:46.860 --> 04:49.550
- Hi.Am I too early?
- No,not at all.

04:49.710 --> 04:51.010
I was just getting things organized for you.

04:51.440 --> 04:52.050
Ok.

04:52.260 --> 04:55.580
- Um,you know,about that
- you can't start today?

04:55.680 --> 04:56.420
You don't want the job?

04:56.470 --> 04:58.220
No!No!I just.

04:59.280 --> 05:02.060
I just want to make sure professor
payne didn't pressure you into this.

05:02.190 --> 05:03.480
He has a way of pushing people.

05:03.620 --> 05:04.710
Yeah,you noticed that,too?

05:04.810 --> 05:05.480
Yeah.

05:05.600 --> 05:08.600
So unless you,um,actually need my help,I...

05:08.710 --> 05:11.690
trust me,when you see the books.we need it.

05:11.810 --> 05:13.920
Um,I'm just gonna grab my laptop,
and then you can get to work.

05:14.020 --> 05:14.490
Ok.

05:16.400 --> 05:19.650
So,how do you and professor payne actually know each other?

05:19.690 --> 05:21.950
Oh,we have some of the same.interests.

05:22.160 --> 05:22.990
Oh,my god!

05:23.630 --> 05:25.690
Oh!Oh,my god!

05:25.820 --> 05:26.580
They're all over me!

05:26.620 --> 05:30.040
What is this?!What is this?!What is this?!

05:30.170 --> 05:31.140
Get them off of me!

05:37.720 --> 05:39.700
Oh,my god!

05:40.380 --> 05:41.670
Are you ok?

05:41.960 --> 05:42.650
Oh,my god,melinda!

05:42.770 --> 05:43.940
- Go get jim.
- Ok.

05:45.080 --> 05:46.050
You're ok.

05:53.520 --> 05:55.380
Finish it!

05:57.150 --> 05:59.460
Finish it!

06:06.920 --> 06:08.310
Delia: He was already on his way over.

06:08.400 --> 06:10.270
Yeah,you could hear that crash
all the way across the square.

06:10.680 --> 06:12.140
Hey there,hi.My name's jim.

06:13.890 --> 06:15.800
All right,that's going to be sore for a little while.

06:16.260 --> 06:17.720
You were very lucky that that's safety glass.

06:17.930 --> 06:19.010
That could have been a lot worse.

06:19.940 --> 06:23.940
Assuming how the definition of luck changes
depending on how bad yours is.

06:24.080 --> 06:26.990
Yeah,right,being attacked by a swarm of flies,not lucky.

06:27.690 --> 06:29.260
These things happen to you a lot?

06:29.910 --> 06:31.710
Daily,yeah.

06:32.620 --> 06:34.130
What kind of things,for example?

06:38.110 --> 06:38.910
Thanks,delia.

06:39.050 --> 06:41.780
Melinda will be back any minute
with some more ice for your arm.

06:42.100 --> 06:43.760
Um,you know what,actually,I'm fine.

06:43.890 --> 06:45.630
I'll just ice it back at the dorm.

06:47.520 --> 06:51.220
I think you should come to the station with me
and let me take a better look at that.

06:51.720 --> 06:52.830
You know what,it's ok.

06:52.930 --> 06:54.090
But thank you for everything.

06:54.210 --> 06:55.980
At least let me drive you home.

06:57.170 --> 06:58.690
No,I have a car.

06:59.300 --> 07:00.040
It's ok.

07:00.170 --> 07:01.310
Thank you.

07:08.520 --> 07:10.330
So did you get a chance to debrief her?

07:10.450 --> 07:12.370
No,she was gone before I got back.

07:12.720 --> 07:15.270
Jim said she couldn't have gotten out of here fast enough.

07:15.370 --> 07:17.450
Now,you're thinking this has something do with her father,right?

07:17.550 --> 07:19.950
That's the first thing I thought of,
and the second,frankly.

07:20.040 --> 07:21.690
I mean,her father died 4 years ago.

07:21.780 --> 07:24.290
That's right around the time kylie started
going to rockland university.

07:24.370 --> 07:26.050
So why would he suddenly appear now?

07:26.140 --> 07:27.810
Maybe he's disappointed in her studies.

07:27.890 --> 07:29.680
I mean,she comes from a long line of academics.

07:29.780 --> 07:31.660
Her grandfather founded the economics department.

07:31.780 --> 07:36.620
Her father was a consultant for the world bank
before he retired to teach at rockland U.

07:36.730 --> 07:38.670
Her brother just graduated summa cum laude from here.

07:38.740 --> 07:41.090
The ghost said "finish it.

07:41.340 --> 07:42.790
" I mean,I guess that could mean college.

07:42.830 --> 07:45.150
Yeah,spoken just like ben,except for the plastic head part.

07:45.260 --> 07:48.610
It makes me wonder,if it is her father,
why he wouldn't just talk to me directly.

07:48.720 --> 07:50.160
And what's with all the weird hauntings?

07:50.240 --> 07:54.480
I mean,the heavy breathing,the doll,the flies,
it's all gotta be a symbol of some kind.

07:54.580 --> 07:56.440
Does it have anything to do with what he used to teach?

07:56.560 --> 07:58.750
No,he was an economist,not an entomologist.

07:58.840 --> 08:00.190
They're the ones that study bugs.

08:00.750 --> 08:01.810
I'm aware of that.

08:01.890 --> 08:02.540
Oh,I'm sorry.

08:02.650 --> 08:04.430
I'm always teaching,I can't help it.You know?

08:04.510 --> 08:07.300
The fact of the matter is,economists,they never speak in metaphor.

08:07.380 --> 08:09.190
That's probably why I never cut it as one.

08:09.270 --> 08:11.550
You know,nobody ever knew what the heck I was talking about.

08:11.620 --> 08:13.000
And that's different now in what way?

08:13.110 --> 08:14.090
That's very funny.

08:14.270 --> 08:18.140
Look,maybe we should just find out from kylie
if she knows anyone who died more recently.

08:18.220 --> 08:20.780
Great.That would be thanatology,the study of the dead.

08:22.500 --> 08:26.950
Look,I know that this is hard to talk about,
but when I met you,

08:27.060 --> 08:30.030
I heard a really strange.breathing noise.

08:30.160 --> 08:31.700
I really want to help you.

08:31.760 --> 08:33.179
You heard it,too,didn't you?

08:33.409 --> 08:34.820
What if I did,what does that mean?

08:35.309 --> 08:36.870
I don't know,have you heard it before?

08:38.260 --> 08:39.539
On occasion.

08:39.970 --> 08:40.870
Since when?

08:42.169 --> 08:45.380
Uh,a few months ago,when my scholarship got revoked.

08:45.510 --> 08:47.860
I'm assuming it has something to do with stress.

08:48.140 --> 08:49.030
Why?

08:51.900 --> 08:56.440
Because I can see ghosts,
and I think there's one haunting you.

08:58.410 --> 09:00.040
Ok.

09:01.430 --> 09:02.520
wow.

09:03.900 --> 09:07.980
I don't want to sound rude,but,um,
you're saying you've seen a ghost around me?

09:08.080 --> 09:12.430
I couldn't see his face,
but he was wearing a hat and a dark overcoat.

09:12.510 --> 09:14.320
Does that sound familiar?

09:16.460 --> 09:20.250
You saw a ghost in a hat and dark overcoat?

09:21.000 --> 09:23.500
- Do you know what you sound like?- Yes.

09:24.500 --> 09:27.430
Yes,I do,but if you could just go with me on it.

09:28.860 --> 09:29.930
Flies.

09:30.550 --> 09:34.020
the doll,um,weird breathing noise.

09:34.040 --> 09:35.870
Does that mean anything to you?

09:36.010 --> 09:39.330
I mean.the doll talked to you.

09:39.400 --> 09:40.540
I know you saw it.

09:41.510 --> 09:42.540
It was a talking doll.

09:42.640 --> 09:43.710
No,it was a ghost.

09:44.150 --> 09:46.680
talking to you,and it said,"finish it.

09:47.570 --> 09:48.550
" What does that mean?

09:48.730 --> 09:49.560
Finish what?

09:50.420 --> 09:51.910
I think this conversation.

09:52.050 --> 09:53.350
I have to go.

09:54.810 --> 09:56.740
Kylie,I really want to help you.

09:57.230 --> 09:59.310
Has anyone around you died recently?

10:00.200 --> 10:02.450
No,not really,actually.

10:04.190 --> 10:06.930
Could this have anything to do with your dad?

10:08.240 --> 10:10.760
Could scaring you be his way of getting you to finish?

10:10.850 --> 10:14.070
Stop it.Don't talk about my dad.

10:14.430 --> 10:15.810
It's bad enough that I've lost him.

10:15.910 --> 10:17.790
Don't make him into some freak ghost.

10:18.420 --> 10:20.700
And by the way,about that job,I quit.

10:32.630 --> 10:33.320
She's scared.

10:33.440 --> 10:36.350
And she's hiding something,
but I'm never going to know what it is,

10:36.430 --> 10:38.060
because I'm never going to see her again.

10:38.760 --> 10:39.830
You're too hard on yourself.

10:39.940 --> 10:41.590
I should have known just to back off,you know?

10:41.680 --> 10:43.590
Even the word "ghost" was wigging her out.

10:43.680 --> 10:45.400
This is not your fault,all right?

10:45.490 --> 10:48.250
She was probably terrified by one of payne's lectures,right?

10:48.950 --> 10:50.760
Nice try.Thanks.

11:29.100 --> 11:30.500
Mel,what's wrong?

11:32.630 --> 11:33.680
Wait a minute.

11:35.390 --> 11:38.690
Wait a minute,it's just like that
scene from that japanese horror film!

11:39.460 --> 11:39.960
What was?

11:40.110 --> 11:41.400
The vision I just had!

11:42.600 --> 11:43.830
Flies!

11:43.940 --> 11:45.920
Amityville horror,or the fly!

11:46.190 --> 11:47.090
The...the doll.

11:47.720 --> 11:49.940
Puppet master,or chucky!

11:50.290 --> 11:51.470
The overcoat.

11:51.760 --> 11:53.000
Oh,my god,the overcoat.

11:53.130 --> 11:54.350
Just pick one.

11:54.900 --> 11:58.350
I can't believe i r-neve-I can't believe I didn't see it!

11:58.460 --> 11:59.110
See what?

11:59.300 --> 12:00.670
The hauntings.

12:01.440 --> 12:03.590
They're all scenes from hvir moorroes.

12:05.510 --> 12:06.320
Let's narrow this down.

12:06.430 --> 12:10.690
We need to find someone who's close to you
that died recently that was a horror film buff.

12:10.720 --> 12:11.820
Anything?

12:12.040 --> 12:14.290
Well,what do you expect?

12:14.370 --> 12:16.450
I expect you to tell me the truth if you want help.

12:16.550 --> 12:20.330
Look,if melinda says you have a ghost,hey,you have a ghost.

12:20.930 --> 12:23.440
Ok,so what if I have one?

12:23.540 --> 12:24.810
What...what's the deal?

12:24.890 --> 12:25.970
What does that mean?

12:26.070 --> 12:29.440
Well,ghosts,if they're here,
it's usually because they have unfinished business.

12:30.070 --> 12:31.220
- Like what?
- Whatever.

12:31.310 --> 12:32.590
It could be anything with a loved one.

12:32.690 --> 12:35.510
It could be unresolved issues of guilt,anger,forgiveness.

12:35.710 --> 12:39.190
Can.this ghost hurt me?

12:39.330 --> 12:42.390
Actually,if they get angry,they can get pretty nasty.

12:43.980 --> 12:45.380
What aren't you telling me,kylie?

12:45.500 --> 12:46.760
There's something you're not telling me.

12:46.870 --> 12:47.920
Did somebody close to you die?

12:48.010 --> 12:49.010
I need to know.

12:49.110 --> 12:53.390
No,I've known people to die,yeah,
but no one close or anything.

12:53.480 --> 12:53.990
Hey,kylie.

12:54.730 --> 12:55.750
Cram session.

12:55.860 --> 12:56.820
Let's get a move on.

12:56.960 --> 12:57.570
I have to go.

12:57.710 --> 12:59.910
I don't want to be the first sloan to not graduate.

13:03.620 --> 13:04.560
Are you at the film school yet?

13:04.650 --> 13:05.820
Did you get any answers?

13:05.900 --> 13:07.810
Rick: Yes,nothing happened,no one died.

13:07.890 --> 13:11.780
I'm telling you,no faculty members,
no janitors,no students,nothing.

13:11.870 --> 13:14.510
If something like that happened,
it would have been all over the campus.

13:14.580 --> 13:18.760
It's not,uh,it's not like we drop
like flies around here,no pun intended.

13:18.850 --> 13:21.440
Well,aren't there any students that are into the genre?

13:21.500 --> 13:23.580
I mean,there is a class or a club or anything?

13:23.670 --> 13:24.200
I'm looking.

13:24.280 --> 13:25.670
I'm at the bulletin board now.

13:25.750 --> 13:28.870
There's a flyer up here for musical theater club.

13:29.120 --> 13:30.280
That's spooky.

13:30.410 --> 13:31.210
Keep looking.

13:31.250 --> 13:33.990
What else do I have?I have a missing kitty.

13:34.610 --> 13:36.170
All right,this is different.

13:36.820 --> 13:40.930
"Scared sane... "we're holding auditions
for a new kind of horror film.

13:41.020 --> 13:43.170
"Ever wonder why some movies terrify you?

13:43.540 --> 13:47.270
"Are you brave enough to enter your own personal horror
"to see what lies within?

13:47.360 --> 13:49.190
Enlightenment awaits.

13:50.010 --> 13:51.560
" Sounds like a real horror buff.

13:51.650 --> 13:53.210
Is there a name,phone number,anything?

13:53.290 --> 13:56.800
Let's see,auditions are at
some downtown production facility.

13:56.900 --> 14:00.250
There's a name,toby bates,
but as far as a number goes,you're out of luck.

14:00.370 --> 14:01.660
It's a couple months old.

14:01.940 --> 14:03.580
Well,fax it over and I'll check it out.

14:03.610 --> 14:05.020
- Ok.
- Thanks.

14:06.760 --> 14:07.880
Hangs up phone Toby.

14:33.090 --> 14:34.460
Ringing Toby?

14:37.640 --> 14:39.130
I'm looking for toby bates.

14:56.410 --> 14:57.420
Hello?

14:58.900 --> 14:59.970
Is anyone there?

15:08.700 --> 15:10.880
Why do I always
get the scary stuff?

15:29.460 --> 15:30.500
Who are you?

15:40.660 --> 15:42.390
Oh, you want to play?

15:42.830 --> 15:44.130
Is that it?

15:50.270 --> 15:51.090
Ok.

15:51.680 --> 15:53.100
So which one is this?

15:53.710 --> 15:55.630
The maze from the shining,
children of the corn,

15:55.680 --> 15:57.720
or the spaceship from alien?

15:58.040 --> 15:59.100
What?

16:09.280 --> 16:10.140
Who are you?

16:24.500 --> 16:25.720
So what is this?

16:27.400 --> 16:29.300
The maze from the shining,
children of the corn

16:29.320 --> 16:31.460
or the spaceship
from alien? What?

16:36.280 --> 16:37.750
Oh, you want to play?

16:37.750 --> 16:48.150
Oh, you want to play?

16:56.330 --> 16:58.670
Ok, here it is,
toby bates' obit.

16:58.700 --> 17:01.010
"Guerilla filmmaker
falls to his death."

17:01.040 --> 17:02.250
This happened 3 months ago.

17:02.270 --> 17:04.300
Oh, that's right, when kylie
said the hauntings started.

17:04.319 --> 17:05.630
She said no one
close to her died.

17:05.650 --> 17:08.200
We should ask her if
she knew this kid toby.

17:08.230 --> 17:10.640
It says he wasn't a student,
so that's not their connection.

17:10.660 --> 17:12.430
He was just a kid
shooting a film.

17:12.640 --> 17:14.540
Yeah, lots and lots
of film apparently.

17:14.560 --> 17:16.619
There's massive amounts
of files on this computer.

17:16.640 --> 17:19.119
Thank goodness you had the
mental fortitude to steal it.

17:19.240 --> 17:20.690
Hey, I did not steal it.

17:20.710 --> 17:23.210
This ghost wanted my help,
led me to that editing bay,

17:23.240 --> 17:24.780
and in fact, probably
wanted me to take it.

17:24.790 --> 17:25.440
What I still want to know is

17:25.480 --> 17:27.839
what are we going to
do about skippy here.

